{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1103: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $A$ be an infinite sequence of integers such that every $n\\in A+A$ is squarefree. How fast must $A$ grow? Current best: In \\cite{Er81h} he asked whether there is an infinite sequence of integers $A$ such that, for every $a\\in A$ and prime $p$, if\\[a\\equiv t\\pmod{p^2}\\]then $1\\leq t<p^2/2$. A superior lower bound of $a_j \\gg j^{15/11-o(1)}$ had earlier been found by Konyagin \\cite{Ko04} when considering the finite case [1109]. Prize: no. OEIS: A392164. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_66a027900fa8c250","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1103 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_7f926bec46e6a061","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1103.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_66a027900fa8c250","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1103","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_7f926bec46e6a061","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1103","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_7f926bec46e6a061","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_66a027900fa8c250","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc1